While the staff were very attentive and friendly, it seemed like the restaurant wasn't properly managing their products: they were completely out of black beans, had no prepared chicken or sofritas, and the corn salsa was not Chipotle corn salsa- it was literally just corn without the onions and cilantro in the normal recipe.  It was later in the evening and it seemed like they had already tried to close up shop far before they were actually "closed".  The customer in front of me ordered a chicken burrito and was still waiting for it to be cooked even after I had gotten my food, eaten and left.  That said, it was well taken care of, clean and with ample seating available.  It's not exactly conveniently located when it comes to public transportation but is walkable from other stops nearby.  I would definitely go back, but hope that they will have their food in stock and not skimp on quality for customers who come later in their operating hours.

I've been trying to buy my lunch at this Chipotle place near my work lately to support them knowing that the business has been undergoing difficult times lately. Today I had a late lunch break (got to this location at 1:45pm), the place was quite empty - no lunch rush hour line, - just a few people at tables and one person at the counter making her purchase. Despite the very slow time, they were out of chicken (what I needed), which made me stand there and wait  when the chicken is ready by letting other customers who did not want chicken go before me. This wait allowed me observe how the employees were trying to figure out the order (several items) that the lady before me requested. There was quite a lot of confusion from their side to figure out what how she needed her order be done.Maybe her order was too complicated (although it looked like she requested it online with all the instructions and came pick it up, and it was just not ready), or maybe the place needs a better manager to make sure things are in order. I tend to think it is the latter! Chipotle, you need better service. Especially now that your sales are going rapidly down!
